---
description: Retrieval-augmented generation and knowledge base rules
globs: ai/**, rag/**, retrieval/**, embeddings/**, vector/**, ingestion/**, knowledge/**
---

AI stack:
- OpenAI API for embeddings and text generation (chat/completions).
- Supabase (or dedicated vector store) for vector search over knowledge chunks.

RAG architecture:
- Separate ingestion, parsing, chunking, embedding, indexing, retrieval, reranking, context assembly, and answer generation.
- Keep retrieval logic independent from answer generation logic.
- Preserve source metadata for traceability (help center, product docs, FAQ, past tickets, internal wiki).

RAG rules:
- Never dump raw full documents into prompts when chunking is expected.
- Use deterministic chunking strategies unless explicitly experimenting.
- Maintain chunk metadata: source, page, section, title, tenant, timestamps.
- Prefer source attribution/citations in outputs for trust and traceability.
- Add configurable retrieval parameters: top_k, filters, score thresholds, reranking options.
- Support multi-document search and follow-up question understanding; use conversation context when building queries.

Knowledge base management (see PRD):
- Support document upload, PDF ingestion, website scraping, auto chunking, embedding generation, version control.
- Ingest from help center articles, product documentation, FAQ, past support tickets, internal wiki.
- Normalize and sanitize extracted text; preserve source identity and version.

Answering expectations:
- Ground answers in retrieved context; handle no-context and low-confidence gracefully.
- Avoid hallucinating unavailable facts; return structured outputs where the product requires it.
- Support multi-language responses where configured.

Do not:
- Mix ingestion code with runtime answer generation in the same module.
- Make retrieval behavior impossible to inspect or tune.
- Hide retrieval failures silently.